  <section class="band faq">
    <div class="section-heading"><p class="eyebrow">Water heater FAQ</p><h2>Common questions before calling for water heater repair</h2></div>
    <details><summary>Do you repair water heaters in Brampton?</summary><p>Yes. Fateh Plumbing & Electric helps with water heater repair in Brampton, including no hot water, leaking tanks, inconsistent temperature, pilot or ignition issues, and replacement planning.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Is a leaking water heater an emergency?</summary><p>A leaking water heater can be urgent if water is spreading, the tank is actively leaking, or the shutoff valve does not stop the water. If water is moving quickly, call the <a href="emergency-plumber.html">emergency plumber</a> page or phone number right away.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Why do I have no hot water?</summary><p>No hot water can be caused by a failed heating element, pilot or ignition issue, gas supply issue, tripped breaker, thermostat problem, or an aging tank.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Should I repair or replace my water heater?</summary><p>Repair may make sense for minor parts or connection issues. Replacement may be better when the tank is leaking, old, badly corroded, unreliable, or not meeting household hot water demand.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Can a plumber fix rusty or smelly hot water?</summary><p>Rusty, discoloured, or smelly hot water can come from the tank, anode rod, sediment, or piping. If nearby pipes are part of the problem, see <a href="pipe-repair.html">pipe repair</a>.</p></details>
    <details><summary>What if I see water around the heater but cannot find the leak?</summary><p>Water may come from the tank, relief valve, drain valve, nearby pipes, condensation, or another hidden source. If the source is unclear, <a href="leak-detection.html">leak detection</a> can help narrow it down.</p></details>
  </section>

